.TH "qmi_handle_init" 9 "qmi_handle_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qmi_handle_init \- initialize a QMI client handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qmi_handle_init
.BI "(struct qmi_handle *qmi "  ","
.BI "size_t recv_buf_size "  ","
.BI "const struct qmi_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "const struct qmi_msg_handler *handlers "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qmi" 12
QMI handle to initialize
.IP "recv_buf_size" 12
maximum size of incoming message
.IP "ops" 12
reference to callbacks for QRTR notifications
.IP "handlers" 12
NULL-terminated list of QMI message handlers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This initializes the QMI client handle to allow sending and receiving QMI
messages. As messages are received the appropriate handler will be invoked.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on failure.
